SIMPLE: tumid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tumid
<hw>Tu"mid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>tumidus</ets>,
fr. <ets>tumere</ets> to swell; cf. Skr. <ets>tumra</ets> strong, fat.
Cf. <er>Thumb</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Swelled, enlarged, or
distended; <as>as, a <ex>tumid</ex> leg; <ex>tumid</ex>
flesh.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rising above the level; protuberant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So high as heaved the <qex>tumid</qex> hills.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Swelling in sound or sense; pompous; puffy;
inflated; bombastic; falsely sublime; turgid; <as>as, a <ex>tumid</ex>
expression; a <ex>tumid</ex> style</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Tu"mid*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Tu"mid*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tumidity</ent>⟦br⟧
